article.headline: W. Michigan 85, Buffalo 64
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Michael Redell and Derek Drews each scored 17 points, tying career highs, as Western Michigan defeated Buffalo 85-64 Wednesday night. Drews came off the bench to hit five 3-pointers in the second half, equaling a career mark, as the Broncos won their ninth consecutive home game dating back to last season. Shawntes Gary added 14 points for the Broncos (10-11, 5-3 Mid-American Conference). Yassin Idbihi led Buffalo (9-12, 1-7) with 13 points and seven rebounds, although he was held short of a double-double for the first time in four games. He moved into seventh place on the school's all-time scoring list with 1,342 points. Parnell Smith came off the bench to score 12 for the Bulls, who lost their fifth straight. Buffalo had been averaging 6.4 3-pointers per game but went 0-for-11 from beyond the arc Wednesday. The Broncos scored 33 points off 22 Bulls turnovers. Western Michigan center Joe Reitz had a game-high 10 rebounds, although the Broncos were outrebounded 31-26. Buffalo led just once, 2-0, on two free throws by Andy Robinson in the first minute. After that, the Broncos dominated and used a nine-point run to gain a 10-point advantage less than nine minutes into the game.
